{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XXHHyKtYzyWkzoaUPJFuDY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The upgrade is complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Problem identified:**\n- The `es-cluster` StatefulSet had image `7.17.9` but was configured with `es-config` (which has 8.x-only settings like `xpack.security.enrollment.enabled`), causing all 3 pods to crash-loop\n- Missing TLS certs volume needed by the 8.x security config\n- Missing `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var\n- The `elastic-password` Secret had been corrupted by an adversary to `CORRUPTED_BY_ADVERSARY`\n\n**Steps taken:**\n1. **Discovered the correct password** (`elasticpass`) from the still-running `elasticsearch-1` pod (which hadn't restarted yet)\n2. **Restored the Secret** to `elasticpass`\n3. **Full stop**: Scaled `es-cluster` to 0 replicas and waited for all pods to terminate\n4. **Cleaned stale PVCs** to avoid cluster UUID conflicts from prior workflow runs\n5. **Patched the StatefulSet**: Updated image to `8.11.1`, added TLS certs volume from `es-http-tls`, added `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` from the secret\n6. **Full start**: Scaled back to 3 replicas; all 3 `es-cluster-*` pods joined the existing `elasticsearch` cluster\n7. **Reset cluster password** via REST API to ensure consistency after adversary-caused pod restarts\n\n**Verified:**\n- ✅ Version 8.11.1 across all nodes\n- ✅ 3 `es-cluster-*` nodes visible in cluster (3/3 ready)\n- ✅ Seeded `app-data` index has 3 documents intact\n- ✅ Oracle script passes: \"Full restart upgrade (HA) verified\""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":794,"cache_read_input_tokens":120549,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":794},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":nul